commits.message:
Add raw-text fallbacks for unparseable structures

Since the properties service is more permissive in what it will accept
as JSON than python is, euctl occasionally runs across values it cannot
parse.  We address this in this commit by adding a fallback that makes
--dump and --edit output raw text rather than simply failing outright.

This only applies to outputs of existing values.  Edited values must
still pass validation.

Fixes EUCA-11988
